		<section class="posts posts-no-stickies">
			<div class="content">
								<article class="entry post-23413 post type-post status-publish hentry tag-center-for-budget-and-policy-priorities tag-club-for-growth tag-corporate-taxes tag-income-tax tag-presidential-election-of-2016 tag-tax-credits-deductions-and-exemptions tag-tax-policy-center tag-tax-shelters tag-trump-donald-j per-trump-donald-j des-corporate-taxes des-income-tax des-presidential-election-of-2016 des-tax-credits-deductions-and-exemptions des-tax-shelters org-center-for-budget-and-policy-priorities org-club-for-growth org-tax-policy-center" id="post-23413">
					<div class="entry-content">
	<div class="inline-module-container show-on-viewport-medium">
	<div class="inlineModule byline">
		<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2015-09-28T17:48:05+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">1:48 <span class="seg">pm ET</span></time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">1:48 <span class="seg">pm ET</span></span>    		<div class="name" data-author="By Maggie Haberman and Patricia Cohen">
    			<address class="author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
								<span class="fn">By Maggie Haberman and Patricia Cohen</span>
							</address>
		</div>
		<div class="shareTools sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet" data-url="//www.nytimes.com/politics/first-draft/2015/09/28/donald-trump-unveils-plan-to-overhaul-tax-code-with-broad-cuts/" data-title="Donald Trump Unveils Plan to Overhaul Tax Code With Broad Cuts" data-description="Donald J. Trump laid out a plan to revamp the tax code, seeking reductions for people at most income levels, including for the highest earners."></div>	</div>
</div><h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title"><a href="//www.nytimes.com/politics/first-draft/2015/09/28/donald-trump-unveils-plan-to-overhaul-tax-code-with-broad-cuts/" rel="bookmark" class="entry-title-link " title="Permanent link to Donald Trump Unveils Plan to Overhaul Tax Code With Broad Cuts">Donald Trump Unveils Plan to Overhaul Tax Code With Broad Cuts</a></h1>	<div class="hide-on-viewport-medium byline">
		<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2015-09-28T17:48:05+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">1:48 <span class="seg">pm ET</span></time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">1:48 <span class="seg">pm ET</span></span>		<div class="name" data-author="By Maggie Haberman and Patricia Cohen" >
			<span class="author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By <address class="vcard first-byline" itemscope itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person" itemid="Maggie Haberman">
					<span class="fn" itemprop="name">Maggie Haberman</span>
				</address> and <address class="vcard second-byline" itemscope itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person" itemid="Patricia Cohen">
					<span class="fn" itemprop="name">Patricia Cohen</span>
				</address>			</span>
		</div>
		<div class="shareTools sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet" data-url="//www.nytimes.com/politics/first-draft/2015/09/28/donald-trump-unveils-plan-to-overhaul-tax-code-with-broad-cuts/" data-title="Donald Trump Unveils Plan to Overhaul Tax Code With Broad Cuts" data-description="Donald J. Trump laid out a plan to revamp the tax code, seeking reductions for people at most income levels, including for the highest earners."></div>	</div>
	<div class="w592"><figure class="promo media video blog-video "
    data-videoid="100000003943340" data-media-action="modal" data-autoplay="" data-embedded="true" aria-label="media" role="group">
        <span class="visually-hidden">Video</span>

    <figcaption class="caption">
        <h4 class="headline">Trump Announces Tax Plan</h4>
		        <div class="caption-video">
                <div class="summary-credit">
            <p class="summary">Donald J. Trump, the Republican presidential candidate, outlined his tax plan on Monday at a news conference in New York.</p>
            <span class="credit video-credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder">
                By REUTERS on                                                    <span class="visually-hidden">Publish Date </span>September 28, 2015.
                            </span>
            <span class="credit photo-credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder">
                                    Photo by Eric Thayer for The New York Times.
                                </span>
        </div>

                    <div class="sharetools-video-container">
                <div id="sharetools-video-tools-100000003943340"
                    class="sharetools sharetools-video-tools">
                    <ul>
                        <li class="sharetool embed-sharetool">
                            <a href="javascript:;" data-share="embed" data-modal-title="">
                                <i class="icon sprite-icon"></i>
                                <span class="sharetool-text ">embed</span>
                            </a>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="sharetools-video-inline-100000003943340"
                    class="sharetools sharetools-video-inline"
                    data-shares="facebook|,twitter|"
                    data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/video/us/politics/100000003943340/trump-announces-tax-plan.html?action=click&amp;contentCollection=us&amp;module=blog-video&amp;region=caption&amp;pgtype=article"
                    data-title="Trump Announces Tax Plan"
                    data-description="Donald J. Trump, the Republican presidential candidate, outlined his tax plan on Monday at a news conference in New York."
                    data-content-type="video">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
            </figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Calling it his personal âwheelhouse,â Donald J. Trump laid out a plan on Monday to revamp the tax code, seeking to reduce taxes for people at most income levels with simplification and by reducing rates, while also eliminating deductions and certain breaks that allow the wealthy and corporations to avoid paying extra.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Standing in the lobby of Trump Tower in Midtown, the real estate developer insisted that wealthy taxpayers like himself would be among the hardest hit <a href="https://www.donaldjtrump.com/images/uploads/trump-tax-reform.pdf">under his plan</a> by eliminating deductions. </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Half of Americans, Mr. Trump said, would pay nothing, since he would end federal income taxes on individuals making less than $25,000 and married couples who file their taxes jointly earning less than $50,000. Currently, roughly 40 percent of lower-income Americans pay no federal income taxes &#8211; a fact that Republicans have long criticized.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">But Mr. Trump would also cut the top tax rate to 25 percent from 39.6 percent, and bring down the corporate tax rate to 15 percent from 35 percent.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Some tax analysts called the plan a boon for the wealthy.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><a href="//www.cbpp.org/chuck-marr">Chuck Marr</a>, director of Federal Tax Policy for the left-leaning Center for Budget and Policy Priorities, said, &#8220;Just like Rubio and Bush, the Trump plan looks to be a huge tax cut for the richest people in the country.&#8221;</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">In particular, Mr. Marr pointed to the huge reduction in pass-through income tax, which can affect mom-and-pop groceries to law partnerships and hedge funds, as well as the elimination of the estate tax. </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><a href="//taxvox.taxpolicycenter.org/author/bobwilliams/">Roberton Williams</a>, at the Tax Policy Center, said: &#8220;It&#8217;s an across-the-board tax cut. Everybodyâs going to benefit to some degree.&#8221; </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">But Mr. Williams noted the wealthy in particular would see a big reduction in their taxes. As for whether the plan would pay for itself, he was skeptical. </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">&#8220;I don&#8217;t see anything in his plan that says he&#8217;ll do enough of that,&#8221; he said referring to cutting loopholes to make up for lost revenue. He, too, was skeptical of the rosy projections of economic growth.  </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">As a group of people held âMake America Great Againâ signs behind him, Mr. Trump told reporters, âIâm not a populist,â despite having harnessed some of that energy from the Republican base by attacking wealthy political donors over the summer months. He insisted that his plan would spur job growth â widening the overall tax base â and make the nation more competitive globally.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Saying his plan targeted the rich, Mr. Trump suggested, for instance, that he wanted to end the âcarried interest loopholeâ used by hedge fund managers and others, which allows them to pay less in taxes by paying capital gains rates on their income. And he highlighted his call to eliminate many tax deductions, which he said would help pay for his plan.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">While declining to be specific, Mr. Trump did say he would retain two deductions &#8211; for mortgage interest and charitable giving &#8211; that are among the costliest to the Treasury, and beneficial to the wealthy.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">&#8220;There will be a major tax reduction,&#8221; he said. &#8220;It&#8217;ll simplify the tax code. It&#8217;ll grow the American economy at a level that it hasn&#8217;t seen for decades.&#8221;</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Mr. Trumpâs tax plan won the ringing endorsement of Grover Norquist, the anti-tax crusader who founded the conservative Americans for Tax Reform organization.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">âThe plan is vintage Ronald Reagan,â Mr. Norquist said. âIt is pro-growth, it is pro-fairness.â</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">After months of bumper-sticker slogans and sound bites, Mr. Norquist said he was pleasantly surprised by the comprehensiveness of Mr. Trumpâs plan. He had a small gripe with how the proposal treats deductibility of business interest expenses but said he could live with the change to how carried interest is taxed considering the deep cuts to personal and corporate tax rates.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">The plan is also âcompletely consistentâ with the pledge not to raise taxes that Mr. Norquist uses to pressure candidates not to break ranks, he said, surmising that Republicans in Congress would be happy to support such a proposal.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"> âAs the centerpiece of a presidential campaign, this is pretty cool,â Mr. Norquist said.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Among the other top items of the plan would be incentives to keep companies from parking money overseas and an end to the deferral of taxes on corporate income earned abroad.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">The anti-tax Club for Growth, which has been airing ads in Iowa against Mr. Trump, took aim at the plan because of how it handled carried interest, eliminated some deductions and taxed corporate income overseas.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">âHad Hillary or Bernie released a similar plan it would be met with overwhelming skepticism,â said the club&#8217;s president, <a href="//www.clubforgrowth.org/staff-members/david-mcintosh/?parent=27">David McIntosh</a>. âRecords matter, and Donald Trump has a long history of calling for the largest tax increase in U.S. history, of calling for higher corporate taxes to pay for government-run health care, of loudly advocating for sky-high tariffs that will act as a 25 percent-35 percent sales tax on every family budget, and of using Obama-like rhetoric to claim that higher taxes should be imposed on those he deems worthy of such punishment.â</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">While the news conference was full, some of the national media who showed up for Mr. Trumpâs recent appearance announcing he had signed a pledge not to run as a third-party candidate did not appear at Mondayâs event.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Many who were in the crowd, forming a backdrop for the cameras, had come downstairs from Mr. Trumpâs offices. Some others were tourists, who said they happened to be in the building and decided to take part. </p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><em>Alan Rappeport contributed reporting.</em></p>
			<div class="nyt-article-promo">
								<div class="w190">
					<a href="//www.nytimes.com/2015/09/29/upshot/trump-plan-is-tax-cut-for-the-rich-even-hedge-fund-managers.html?ref=first-draft"><img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2015/09/29/us/29UP-TRUMPTAX/29UP-TRUMPTAX-thumbWide.jpg" width="190" height="126" alt="Trump Plan Is Tax Cut for the Rich, Even Hedge Fund Managers" /></a>
				</div>
                				<h4><a href="//www.nytimes.com/2015/09/29/upshot/trump-plan-is-tax-cut-for-the-rich-even-hedge-fund-managers.html?ref=first-draft">Trump Plan Is Tax Cut for the Rich, Even Hedge Fund Managers</a></h4>
				<p class="nyt-article-byline">By JOSH BARRO</p>
				<p class="nyt-article-summary">Donald Trumpâs proposal does not live up to the populist language he offered on taxes all summer.</p>
			</div>
			
